[div class=p 
	"This version of 
	[em 
		"Donkey Kong
	]em
	" (informally known as 
	[em 
		"Donkey Kong '94
	]em
	", due to its 1994 release date) follows the same premise as the original game from the 1980s, in that Mario is tasked with rescuing Pauline from the eponymous Donkey Kong. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Besides adding over 90 additional stages to the original 4 stages, this release also introduces many new game-play mechanics which both help and hinder Mario from reaching his goal.  Some of these new elements are patterned off concepts from other 
	[em 
		"Mario
	]em
	" games including 
	[em 
		"Donkey Kong Jr.
	]em
	", 
	[em 
		"SMB
	]em
	", 
	[em 
		"SMB 2 (USA)
	]em
	", and 
	[em 
		"SMB 3
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The authors abuse a glitch in the save system which causes the game to act as if it completed a later checkpoint up until the final one at 9-5.  See the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=authors' comments|href=/8587S)
	" for more information.
	$LF
]div
